Kakamega, Kenya: Likuyani MP Enoch Kibunguchy suffered a double tragedy following the loss his mother Dinah Nasike, 88, and uncle Hillary Wafula on the same day. Dr Kibunguchy said his mother, who had been sick for the past five years, was first diagnosed with diabetes and later high blood pressure before she suffered a stroke. Mr Wafula will be laid to rest on August 27 in Kitale while Ms Nasike will be buried on September 3 in Likuyani.